            "title": "Soziale Ungleichheit und die Hermeneutik des Leibes: Ein sozialpsychologischer Kulturvergleich zwischen Deutschland und Brasilien",
            "abstract": "Social inequality, Unconscious, Collective unconscious, Gender, Semiotics, Psychoanalysis, Socialisation, Socialisation theory, Pierre Bourdieu, Alfred Lorenzer, Charles Sanders Peirce, Depth hermeneutics, Hermeneutics, Body. - The objective of this doctoral thesis is to contribute to a better understanding for the emergence and perpetuation of social inequality as well as for the creation of social change from a socio-psychological perspective. The theoretical reflections as well as the empirical analysis, of which the thesis is composed, focus on the interplay of objective social conditions and bodily psychical structures, when explaining the evolution of social order. In the theoretical part of the thesis a psychoanalytic semiotic concept of habitus, linking different theoretical approaches, i.e. Bourdieu's concept of habitus, the socialisation theory of Lorenzer and Peirce's theory of signs, is developed. The unconscious, understood as social phenomenon, which takes its starting point in the various bodily psychical interactions between a child and its parents, plays a central role within the established concept. The empirical study with female university professors and cleaning personnel in Germany and Brasil reveals the unconscious, preconscious and conscious dimensions of the women's habitus providing for the maintenance of social inequality as well as for social change.",
